## P0: Systemd & Infrastructure Hardening (MUST HAVE)

### Problem
Systemd units were **deferred** in v0.4.26. Production cannot run without hardened service definitions.

### Work Required

| Task | Status | Owner |
|------|--------|-------|
| Audit all systemd units for security best practices | 🔴 Not started | Agent B |
| Add `PrivateTmp=yes`, `NoNewPrivileges=yes`, `ProtectSystem=strict` | 🔴 Not started | Agent B |
| Move inline secrets out of `.service` files | 🔴 Not started | Agent B |
| Use `EnvironmentFile=/etc/aitbc/%N.env` for secrets | 🔴 Not started | Agent B |
| Add systemd watchdog (`WatchdogSec=30`, `NotifyAccess=all`) | 🔴 Not started | Agent B |
| Limit resources (`MemoryMax`, `CPUQuota`) | 🔴 Not started | Agent B |
| Add restart policy: `Restart=on-failure`, `RestartSec=5` | 🔴 Not started | Agent B |

### Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All services run as non-root user
- [ ] No secrets in `/etc/systemd/system/*.service`
- [ ] `systemctl status` shows clean security profile
- [ ] OOM conditions are handled gracefully

